you can kill someone with that.

74
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:12,604
Don't worry. I'll be careful. Come here!

75
00:05:12,687 --> 00:05:13,772
-Mom.
-Come over here.

76
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,232
Dad, save me.

77
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:17,984
How did you lose it this time?

78
00:05:18,068 --> 00:05:20,695
I was buying a workbook at a bookstore.

79
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:23,824
Mom, a lot of other kids
lost their bikes there, too.

80
00:05:23,907 --> 00:05:27,619
She was at a bookstore
buying a workbook for studying.

81
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:30,288
The father-and-daughter team
always make me the bad guy.

82
00:05:30,372 --> 00:05:32,666
What's the point in working
on new recipes day and night

83
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:34,543
when you two keep spending all the money?

84
00:05:34,626 --> 00:05:36,878
Come on, we don't spend all of it.

85
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,505
Plus, I help you a lot.

86
00:05:38,922 --> 00:05:41,216
Buy a new bike this weekend.

87
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:43,718
-Don't whine about taking the bus.
-What?

88
00:05:45,637 --> 00:05:46,513
No.

89
00:05:50,183 --> 00:05:52,477
I should've just let her buy me
a new bike.

90
00:05:53,311 --> 00:05:56,565
Why am I going through this trouble
to ride on the back of Heon's bike?

91
00:05:56,648 --> 00:05:59,234
My legs hurt.

92
00:06:04,573 --> 00:06:07,701
Hey, Brother.
It's tough without a bicycle, isn't it?

93
00:06:08,577 --> 00:06:11,454
I can't complain. I brought it on myself.

94
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:13,623
I can take you to school
until you get a new bike.

95
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:15,292
No, it's okay.

96
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:18,336
I have a question.

97
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:21,756
What do you want others to do for you
when you're sad?

98
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:23,300
Well, I don't know.

99
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:25,886
When I'm sad,

100
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:29,014
wouldn't it mean the most
to just keep that person company?

101
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:31,057
Oh, really?

102
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:32,183
Yes.

103
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:42,611
I'LL HELP YOU!

104
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:49,576
Everyone did a great job.

105
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:53,914
So many of your assignments touched me.

106
00:06:54,789 --> 00:06:57,292
Especially Hui-ji's and Cha Heon's.

107
00:06:57,584 --> 00:07:01,212
It didn't seem like
they were written by students.

108
00:07:01,296 --> 00:07:03,048
I almost thought you were writers.

109
00:07:03,340 --> 00:07:04,299
Speaking of which,

110
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:07,510
Sol-i, would you mind reading this?

111
00:07:09,638 --> 00:07:11,473
-Pardon?
-Read it out loud.

112
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:15,060
Okay.

113
00:07:17,938 --> 00:07:19,230
NAME: CHA HEON

114
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:26,363
"One day when I was eight,

115
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:29,199
I got lost in an unfamiliar place.

116
00:07:29,908 --> 00:07:32,744
I felt like crying,

117
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:35,580
but I held back my tears,
saying I would never cry.

118
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:38,166
After some time passed,

119
00:07:39,084 --> 00:07:41,002
-<i>my father came to look for me.</i>"
-Heon!

120
00:07:41,211 --> 00:07:42,337
Dad!

121
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:45,215
"<i>I burst into tears and ended up crying.</i>"

122
00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:47,842
-"<i>My father simply looked at me.</i>"
-It's okay.

123
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:50,136
-"<i>He gave me a warm hug.</i>"
-It's all right.

124
00:07:51,346 --> 00:07:53,974
"<i>Then, my father and I</i>
<i>went to a Chinese restaurant</i>

125
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:57,143
<i>and ate </i>jajangmyeon<i>, my favorite dish.</i>

126
00:07:58,144 --> 00:07:59,938
<i>My father's hand,</i>

127
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:03,984
<i>which I held all the way back home,</i>
<i>was very warm.</i>

128
00:08:11,366 --> 00:08:14,869
It was the longest day
I spent with my father,

129
00:08:15,787 --> 00:08:19,916
who was always busy with work."

130
00:08:26,715 --> 00:08:28,717
Do you still have <i>jajangmyeon</i> with him?

131
00:08:36,725 --> 00:08:40,854
Heon, my mom will make bulgogi tomorrow,
do you want to come?

132
00:08:42,647 --> 00:08:43,565
No.

133
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,818
Then, can I ride this bike with you?

134
00:08:47,569 --> 00:08:49,904
I'll be quiet and won't bother you.

135
00:08:50,155 --> 00:08:52,240
I'm super light like a feather.

136
00:08:52,449 --> 00:08:53,324
What do you say?

137
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:57,203
You can take the bike, then.

138
00:08:58,496 --> 00:08:59,539
Where are you going?

139
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:02,959
Can't I come with you?

140
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:05,837
Don't follow me.

141
00:09:46,169 --> 00:09:47,253
All right.

142
00:09:48,213 --> 00:09:50,715
It'll be hard for Heon
to prepare everything on his own.

143
00:09:50,799 --> 00:09:55,720
And I don't think it's a bad idea
to be in his mom's good books.

144
00:09:57,722 --> 00:10:01,101
What does it feel like to like someone?

145
00:10:01,184 --> 00:10:03,186
Well…

146
00:10:04,813 --> 00:10:07,524
When he shows up,
everything around him becomes dark,

147
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:09,984
and he's the only thing that lights up.

148
00:10:10,068 --> 00:10:13,363
Hmm, like the halo effect idols have?

149
00:10:13,446 --> 00:10:14,614
Halo effect.

150
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,719
I didn't order this.

151
00:10:42,392 --> 00:10:43,309
Heon.

152
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:46,688
I ordered it for you.

